      "It seems like in basically any language any time you accept a boolean parameter you should run it through a conversion function like this:\r\n\r\n```\r\nbool convert(something) {\r\n    if (something) return true;\r\n    else return false;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThat way it will match the languages interpretations of booleans."
